website_summaries.verdict: This plastic-based trap avoids many of the problems of cheap wooden traps and comes in a set of four that's ideal for larger areas.
pros: Scientifically designed to deliver the right "snap" velocity
cons: Cheap plastic construction can lead to failure

customer_reviews.title: After 2 weeks we caught a total of 17 rats using 4 traps!  BTW... They really like peanut butter.
customer_reviews.text: Unfortunately our 15 yr old Jack Russel dog passed away this year. He was quite a mouser... Then all of a sudden several rats started appearing in our backyard. The Trapper T-Rex has helped us to control the rat infestation. The traps are lightweight... Some of the rats were able to drag the trap away for many feet before they perished. I fastened small 4"x4" sheet metal electrical box covers to the bottoms of the traps to make them a bit heavier to keep occupants from dragging them away. The electrical box cover I used is called a "4S" cover, and you can get it at any hardware store for about $1.00.
customer_reviews.author: Canyon Country Mike

customer_reviews.title: Tried & true product!
customer_reviews.text: A great product. I've used these for several years. They work perfect for pesky chipmunks. Easy to bait. I use a dab of peanut butter & stick in a couple sunflower seeds. I recommend attaching a loop of twine to the trap then put a sturdy stick through the loop to keep trapped creatures from moving it. I also cover the trap with a cheap wire trash can turned upside down. I cut out an entrance hole in the wire then put the stick through the wire basket and into the loop on the trap. It will insure you won't accidentally trap any birds. Keeps others from touching the trap by accident too.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: For use with SMALL rats only!
customer_reviews.text: These traps are wonderfully simple to use: no precarious bars to fit into trigger holes, you just bait them, cock them and deploy them. HOWEVER, they also aren't as powerful. They are sturdy but twice, they did not kill the rat. I prefer live traps anyway, but needed to use kill traps in this instance. So finding the poor animals injured rather than dispatched humanely was of course grim. And these were not huge rats: they were perhaps 7 inches long, not including their tail. So if you have smaller rats, these are great, but otherwise, forget it and get more traditional traps. And manufacturer, please put more powerful springs in these T-Rex's!
customer_reviews.author: JT

customer_reviews.title: Excellent traps.  Use caution around pets and children.
customer_reviews.text: These work! Good price and well made. I filled the wells with peanut butter and set the traps. Then we stuck a toothpick in one to see how much pressure it would take to set it off. The snap was so forceful that it made me (the one who deliberately set it off!) jump about a mile into the air. Within a couple days we caught our vermin (yuck!) Make sure you place these AWAY from an area children or animals can get to them. They absolutely are forceful enough to break a tiny finger or hurt other body parts. Definitely recommend for their purpose, just be careful when you're prepping them and placing them.
customer_reviews.author: Outspoken RN

customer_reviews.title: Absolute Junk - Buyer Beware - Not a Real T-Rex - Cheap Chinese Knock-off
customer_reviews.text: Works great for one trap. After the first trap, the trigger no longer holds jaws open = throw it away. I bought the four pack and then read the reviews. Big mistake. As soon as I read the reviews, I tried to recall my order but was unable. Now I need to buy a real T-Rex. Anyone know where I can get one? Seller needs to advertise "ONE TIME USE ONLY". Very disappointed, waste of money...
customer_reviews.author: Shepherds

customer_reviews.title: Not built well
customer_reviews.text: Received these traps with high expections. I have caught one rat, since. The others have been set off often, but no rat. After about 5 times of slamming closed the plastic breaks and or gets misaligned and won't set any more. Just caught a rat today in a different trap that uses thick rubber bands. Great, but can't find the dead rat yet. It suffacates them. I forget the name, but it's a long tube with green rubber bands.
customer_reviews.author: Jim

customer_reviews.title: Easy peezy rat squeezy
customer_reviews.text: I had big wood rats tripping over my traditional traps without being caught, so I had to try something new. I used peanut butter with milled oats as bait and the first night the T-Rex traps killed two rats that were bigger than the traps themselves. I like the removable bait cup, it helps control the mess of baiting. Also, I like being able to set the traps without being anywhere near the business end of the trap.
customer_reviews.author: Bryan

customer_reviews.title: Safer for People But Not for Rats
customer_reviews.text: Posted these in our garage a couple of months ago to catch the roof rats that come through there from time to time. The basic classic trap had sprung on my husband's finger, but these are much safer (for people). Successfully caught one rat so far, and it was easy to empty the trap and reload it. Seems to be as effective as a classic trap, but safer to set.
customer_reviews.author: JMS

customer_reviews.title: Two Stars
customer_reviews.text: Work very well to catch and kill chipmunks. Used successfully for several years, UNTIL....recently when we just bought another 4 pack. Someone in their infinite wisdom thought, "Hey! Let's make the bait cup removable! Great. So now the tabs holding the cup into the trap are breaking and the bait cup can no longer stay attached to the trap. We now have 4 useless traps. Will never buy this brand again, and actually, I'd avoid ANY of these types of traps that state removable bait cup. Bad news. As they used to be made, they were extremely effective over and over again - loved these and caught tons of chipmunks. Not anymore.
customer_reviews.author: happymom37

customer_reviews.title: These are the simplest traps to use! I won't ...
customer_reviews.text: These are the simplest traps to use! I won't use anything else. Put a dollop of attractant in the little cup area, set it, and walk away. It kills the rat (or mouse in the smaller mouse traps) instantly! Then we just crimp it open, dump the rodent in the trash and it's ready to go again. I recently heard it's even more of n attractant is you DON'T clean it between uses, as the rodent will smell the previous 'occupant' and come inquiring. So no longer is my son allowed to wash off any blood or 'pieces' after dumping a victim in the trash.
customer_reviews.author: BMK

customer_reviews.title: Good, but not very durable
customer_reviews.text: These work well and are very easy to set, but they aren't the most durable. I had several that broke after a month or so of use. The plastic in the back that holds the spring eventually breaks and then they aren't any good. The good thing though is that they are much easier to set than the old wooden snap traps. I don't feel like I'm going to lose a finger every time I bait it. They also have very good killing power on large rats.
customer_reviews.author: P. Mullis

customer_reviews.title: Sturdy, and works
customer_reviews.text: Worked great. We had tried several smaller traps near our citrus trees without success, but this one works, even for large rats. It’s easy to load, and can be filled from the bottom, as well. Given the correct bait, it will catch them, just be patient. We suggest using gloves when loading it, to avoid putting human scent on the trap. Our best success was with...bacon. Who could resist?
customer_reviews.author: kc

customer_reviews.title: Safe to use
customer_reviews.text: I have been using these for several years now mainly because they are so safe to use - I don't worry about accidentally breaking a finder trying set a rat trap. They also do a good job of trapping rats. They will breakdown given enough time - that is, the plastic will crack or break off but that is a small price to pay compared to several hundred dollars for car or truck repair.
customer_reviews.author: Troutlet

customer_reviews.title: This seems like a "Bait and Switch" scheme from this seller
customer_reviews.text: I bought the 4 pack. Right out of the box, one was broken. I set the other 3 in the attic. I caught one mouse. That trap would not set again. so I through it way. Now I was down to 2 traps left. I went back into the attic to re-position one of the traps. I accidently tripped the trap as I was moving it. Now that trap would not re-set. I had to through this one away also. Now I'm down to one in less than a week. Also, no where on the trap does it display "T-Rex Trap". This seems like a "Bait and Switch" scheme from this seller. Pun intended.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: Very effective
customer_reviews.text: Works better than any snap trap we've ever used. Do tie it to something so that the wounded/trapped/not-dead-yet won't drag it away, and do be prepared to "dispatch" any critters who just get their leg in it. I find it horrifying that this happens, but it does. We use a pellet gun to put them out of their misery. Most kills have been clean however. We tie our traps to pieces of wood. We have also killed several mice in the rat trap.
customer_reviews.author: CynK

customer_reviews.title: easy to use and set
customer_reviews.text: These traps are affordable, easy to use and set, and work great for the bigger rats. The brand you probably see the most is Victor. (The big red V with the mouse in the middle.) Those traps never seem to keep larger rats in them for me. Tomcat makes a similar T-Rex trap but those seem to break after a few uses. These ones I've had the best luck with when it comes to killing larger rats and so far haven't broken.
customer_reviews.author: Lyle

customer_reviews.title: worked as advertised - killed two roof rats
customer_reviews.text: awesome...killed two rats. I bought these based on recommendations from Amazon reviewers and it worked great...I tried a lot of different products for roof rats and this is the only one that killed two of them...throw some peanut butter on the plate and it will get them. I also like the fact that to set the trap, your hands aren't around the "jaw" of the trap. Great product and easy to use.
customer_reviews.author: rchrpwin15

customer_reviews.title: The rats will laugh at you.
customer_reviews.text: These might be okay if screwed down to a piece of wood or something, but they aren't strong enough to instantly kill large rats, and they aren't heavy enough to keep the rats from dragging them. They are fairly sensitive, but I prefer standard traps after using both. Update: after one season of use, these were completely worthless. I have traditional ready traps that have lasted years and still work, but many of these stopped working altogether, and others became so anemic that rats just laughed at them.
customer_reviews.author: Forbes

customer_reviews.title: Great trap, but baiting for success is important.
customer_reviews.text: This works well for rats, but I seem to have either large mice or small rats and if they are mice, they can steal the bait easy without getting caught. The key is to put a smelly bait (my dog's "beggin' strips" have worked best) and put way back in the middle of the trap. This will kill even small mice by forcing them to trigger it. Also try to make sure they can't get the bait from the side. Put paralell with a wall... The trap is powerful and you do need to be careful when baiting.
customer_reviews.author: J. Beehner

customer_reviews.title: Oh My God !  These Work !
customer_reviews.text: ( Don't Lose a Finger ! ) These are TOUGH and STRONG and REALLY WORK ! YIKES ! Be Careful . . . Do it Right . . . and . . . These Will Work ! ( Got rid of all the little scurrying varmints plaguing my basement floor crawl space ! ) Thanks !!!
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: but I don't know if it's from rats or a happy trigger mechanism
customer_reviews.text: All the traps have been triggered about 4 times in the past 2 weeks, but I don't know if it's from rats or a happy trigger mechanism. Two of the traps no longer set because the plastic on the trigger is already worn down. I did catch one rat, but it was still able to make it about two feet away into a crevice to die in spite of having his head caught in the trap.
customer_reviews.author: Lisa V

customer_reviews.title: It works
customer_reviews.text: I placed 1/2 of a tootsie roll in the bait area. Checked they trap the next day and it had a full sized rat in it. These are cheap enough to just throw the whole thing in the trash. I also bought the name brand one because I read that some of the knock off brands don’t work and I didn’t want to take a chance.
customer_reviews.author: A. LaBell

customer_reviews.title: Industrial strength better mousetrap
customer_reviews.text: Be careful of your fingers. This can do real damage. Figure out how it works first before you do anything. You can set this with the press of a lever. No problem. Take the bait cup out from below. No problem. The thing snaps so hard it'll scare the hell out of you. I got a well-fed mouse who thought he was immortal. The next little one got trapped. Had to bash it with a shovel.
customer_reviews.author: Julian Lev

customer_reviews.title: Easy for the Queasy
customer_reviews.text: The Trapper T-Rex did its job. I loaded the bait tray with peanut butter, and within two weeks, the little sucker was caught head first in its jaws. The little beast expired in the trap. Disposal was easy for the queasy. Scooped it all up together, trap and critter, into a plastic bag, and into the dumpster. In essence, the trap becomes a convenient handle when the deed is done. Update 6/5/2015: already caught three rats in the basement of the house since January. I bought four more today.
customer_reviews.author: J. Ho

customer_reviews.title: Rats Beware We'er Going to Geta
customer_reviews.text: I had seen these traps used by professional pest control people. One man said they were the best rat trap he had ever used. Although I must have eventually killed out my woodrat problem before the traps arrived. My game camera has not tripped​ the last 3 nights. One thing I really liked is the ease of operation and the attention to detail. A well thought out traps. I had purchased the Tom-Cat bait block, but the one thing I don't like about most bait blocks is it take too long to kill a rat anywhere from 4 to 5 days. Of course, I absolutely despise rats.
customer_reviews.author: billhigh67

customer_reviews.title: It works, but not always completely
customer_reviews.text: We've trapped ten rats so far. Love the ease of "loading" the trap. My only negative comment is that it doesn't snap as hard as the old fashioned wood and metal type, or the plastic isn't as effective, which means it doesn't always kill the trapped rat. I don't want any animal to suffer, even a rat, and it's unpleasant to have to finish the job.
customer_reviews.author: Reader

customer_reviews.title: This is really easy to set, BUT, about 50% of the time it does NOT kill the rat
customer_reviews.text: UPDATED 1 year later: This is really easy to set, BUT, about 50% of the time it does NOT kill the rat. It ends up capturing half its head or even a leg, and I have to use a shovel to break its neck. I don't want to use poison baits (because of cats and hawks/owls) and I don't even want to think about glues/tapes. I wish someone invented a trap that actually killed rodents. I hate rodents, but no animal should have to suffer for hours first. I've trapped about 30 rats now over the last 2 Winters.
customer_reviews.author: Markus Meier

customer_reviews.title: Another one bites the dust
customer_reviews.text: I have a rat problem outside. I was initially disappointed with this trap, but am now pleased with it's performance. The spring does indeed have enough power to kill a rat. I wasn't succeeding in my efforts to take care of the rats and it wasn't until I placed the trap well into the undergrowth that I met with a confirmed kill. Leaving the trap even partially exposed isn't enough; it's got to be placed under low-lying leaves, where rats like to lurk.
customer_reviews.author: Cautious

customer_reviews.title: It works
customer_reviews.text: I like this trap much better than the old fashion kind with the wood base. It is easy to set and to release. I have caught 2 rats so far and they have all been caught in the neck for a fast, clean kill. It is easy to release the body without having to touch the rat. The bait cup forces the rat to get his head into the trap to get the bait.
customer_reviews.author: my painted lady

customer_reviews.title: They work well but....
customer_reviews.text: But beware: one seller will ship you a cheaper less worthy substitute for the same price as the T-Rex. You'll have to fight them to return what you did not order and not charge you a restocking fee. Order several of The Bell Lab T-Rex if you have lots of rats as trapping one at a time will not end the problem. I used four and my problem was gone. Place them facing a wall. Snickers works well as a bait. The traps are easy to load from the bottom.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: Super Rat Traps
customer_reviews.text: Best traps on the market. They are sturdy and kill rats dead! On one occasion I killed four young rats in two traps (see photo). The first one was not heavy enough to spring it, but when his brother joined him to eat the bait they were both dispatched instantly. I used peanut butter bait to clear out a nest of about a dozen rats last fall/winter and they haven't been back.
customer_reviews.author: D. Baker

customer_reviews.title: Maybe they would have worked fine, but last time I bought the same traps ...
customer_reviews.text: Sorry, but have to give a one star since traps shipped were NOT authentic T-Rex rat traps, but knockoffs. Real T-Rex traps have the labeling "T-Rex" engraved/etched on the traps. And the knockoffs they sent had springs that looked smaller than authentic T-Tex traps. Maybe they would have worked fine, but last time I bought the same traps from the same vendor the real, authentic T-Rexs were shipped. So want the real deal", sorry...
customer_reviews.author: UrbaneCowboy007

customer_reviews.title: I'm pretty sure these are not original T rex traps
customer_reviews.text: I'm pretty sure these are not original T rex traps. Comes in blank plastic wrap. Used it last night and caught a guy in one but he escaped and another one took the bait and didn't even trip the trap : edit: PIECE OF CRAP DO NOT BUY. LUCKY IT'S A 4 PACK CUZ THEY DON'T WORK AS THE DAYS GO BY. GARBAGE
customer_reviews.author: hien le

customer_reviews.title: Best spring trap I have found !!!
customer_reviews.text: I live on a farm, and we are constantly dealing with Norway rats in the livestock sheds and chicken coops. I have used several types of traps, and poison is obviously NOT an option here. These traps work better than anything else I have tried. Just make sure to tie a string or cable (they have a hole for this built in) to the trap and something secure, as the rats will otherwise occasionally take off with them.
customer_reviews.author: Dave T

customer_reviews.title: A Better Mouse Trap.
customer_reviews.text: Been using these for two years. Best rat trap on the market. These are rat killing machines. Couldn't tell you how many I've killed. Time to buy some more. Not because any of them broke (they are well made), but because these things are so effective, I've given them all away. Rat problem? Meet the solution.
customer_reviews.author: Diverjay

customer_reviews.title: Excellent! A rat chewed through the radiator and heater ...
customer_reviews.text: Excellent! A rat chewed through the radiator and heater hoses on my car. Ordered these and the very next day caught that sucker. Easy to use. Way better than traditional. rat traps. There's a small removable cup on the bottom to put the bait in. I used peanut butter. Set these out and there you go.
customer_reviews.author: S. Cleere

customer_reviews.title: Plastic, too small.
customer_reviews.text: They are plastic, I have not c aw caught any rats, but one of the traps disappeared, I guess there is a big ass Rat walking around with one of these traps as bling. They are kind of small too.
customer_reviews.author: Gary Wilds

customer_reviews.title: Not Trapper TRex. Cheap imitations. False Advertising
customer_reviews.text: I bought these based on the title and past experience with REAL Trapper T Rex traps...These are NOT trapper Trex branded traps. No label or branding. Horrible quality cheaper plastic. One wouldn't set out of the box. Two of the three won't stay set in a breezy sunny day. Night and day difference between authentic one and this cheap version. The setting of the trap, the spring tension, the quality just not the same between them. I am returning them. Don't waste your money.
customer_reviews.author: JTH57

customer_reviews.title: Five Stars
customer_reviews.text: put these out yesterday and within 10 minutes had our first rat. wouldn't want to get my finger stuck! UPDATE; they will break 3 or 4 months down the road, but they are doing their job update - for the price you would expect them to last longer. the latching spring is the first to go, and then the spring rusts. i have, however, gotten a number of rats
customer_reviews.author: edgarallencrow

customer_reviews.title: Effective, great value for the money.
customer_reviews.text: Very effective. I sealed up infested area, then set multiple traps using chunks of cooked bacon as bait. Some bait was stolen, but other traps worked as designed. Trap appears humane in that kills are quick. Trap is powerful, but relatively safe to set. Depopulated the infestation in short order using proper trapping guidelines.
customer_reviews.author: Count Zero

customer_reviews.title: Good traps for larger rodents if have a hearts do ...
customer_reviews.text: Good traps for larger rodents if have a hearts do not work for you. You do need to anchor them down for they do disappear on occasion if you do not.Price could be a little better for a four pack.
customer_reviews.author: Bobby Boyd

customer_reviews.title: T-Rex is Bad @#$ Once gets hold it doesn't let go!!
customer_reviews.text: Caught first rat. T-Rex won. I do believe rats are really intelligent. Makes sense that dumb one get weeded out. Clamped his @#% and didn't let go. Watch those fingers. Update caught 2nd rat. I used dog food as bait and caught a rat that night.
customer_reviews.author: Jared Quandt

customer_reviews.title: WARNING:  BEWARE OF ILLEGAL CHEAP COPIES FROM SOME SELLERS!!!
customer_reviews.text: The genuine traps would get 5 stars. The seller "Tropical Accessories" is selling cheap junky copies of the real thing. They are worthless and garbage.
customer_reviews.author: Dad

customer_reviews.title: one trap caught 3 mice. I placed it in ...
customer_reviews.text: one trap caught 3 mice. I placed it in a corner where I thought they were walking by (didn't even bait it) it either caught their leg or tail, one was crushed all the way in the middle. admittedly not very humane, but they were avoiding all the humane traps i'd set
customer_reviews.author: vilegrin

customer_reviews.title: Worth the extra money!
customer_reviews.text: I used the Victor Rat Traps and almost lost a finger plus they didn't catch me any rats. The sticky traps didn't catch me any rats either, but caught my daughter's foot and my dog. These Trapper T-Rex's are great and much more safer! Even though they are a little pricer, they are well worth the investment. It caught me the two rats that I have been trying to get rid of in my house for the past couple weeks!!
customer_reviews.author: K. to the L.

customer_reviews.title: works much better that old fashion wood snap traps
customer_reviews.text: works much better than the wood snap traps, but minus 2 stars because it doesn't always finish the job. Also, use only a small amount of peanut butter on the bait cup - too much and it will interfere with the trigger mechanism underneath.
customer_reviews.author: San Fernando Valley -Los Angeles, CA

customer_reviews.title: They are easy to set and have held up well thus far
customer_reviews.text: We planted some fruit trees a couple of years ago and now they are bearing fruit. The fruit has attracted rats so we had to defend our harvest! We tried the electronic trap with limited success. I then ordered the Trapper T-Rex traps based on reviews. We placed one of the traps by the plum tree and a couple in the planters. We have been catching one each night and two last night. They are easy to set and have held up well thus far.
customer_reviews.author: Lballl

customer_reviews.title: Great rat trap
customer_reviews.text: Great rat trap. I use peanut butter with dry cat food. I think the rats are pretty smart and get use to this thing. Keep moving it around and change the bait often.
customer_reviews.author: claudia murray

customer_reviews.title: Trapper T-Rex Traps
customer_reviews.text: These are the best traps that I have ever used. I have had a problem with flying squirrels getting into my attic. I have spent well over a thousand dollars for the services of an exterminator. No matter what we tried the squirrels would find a new way into the attic. I now uses these traps year round and found the best thing to do is to catch the squirrels when they find a way into my attic. These traps are great.
customer_reviews.author: Robert M. Krause

customer_reviews.title: No Fuss - No Muss
customer_reviews.text: Easy to set up. Significantly easier than the Victor brand which can catch your finger. Since the food source is lower than the trap plate the rat has to reach into the mouth and press on the trap plate. SNAP! The rat is caught and humanely caught and killed. Caught my garage rat within 24 hrs. Disposal is equally quick. Highly recommend.
customer_reviews.author: Ronald T.

customer_reviews.title: Dead Rat
customer_reviews.text: We've had a rat terrorizing us for months, he was taking our glue traps to use as mattresses. He'd even eat the heads off the mice that were caught on them... a real sicko. Thought I'd try these bad boys out since nothing else had worked. Set one up in his stomping grounds, left for the afternoon and came home to a mousy nearly cut in half. Had the kid take care of that (eww) then reset the trap. About 5~10 minutes later the wife heard a snap. Had the kid check it out, caught that rat b*stard by the back of his neck. Took him out instantly. 10 out of 10, would kill rat again.
customer_reviews.author: Jarrad Kippen

customer_reviews.title: Decent. Not 100%
customer_reviews.text: They work. Not always the most sensitive tho. Have had. A couple times where bait was gone and trap hadn't been tripped. But when they trip tho that animal is toast.
customer_reviews.author: USMC24

customer_reviews.title: Set up and baiting is incredibly easy and safe compared to old style wooden rat traps ...
customer_reviews.text: Got these to get rid of chipmunk/gophers in the lawn. Set up and baiting is incredibly easy and safe compared to old style wooden rat traps that could take your finger off. However, it isn't large enough or snap hard enough to kill the larger ones immediately. It worked great on smaller ones but a larger one dragged it around for a while and I had to kill it. Will keep using but wished it worked better on larger ones.
customer_reviews.author: Anonymous

customer_reviews.title: Rats are too smart for this
customer_reviews.text: the rats quickly learned to remove the bait without tripping the trap. I used peanut butter, thinking it would be too sticky, but each morning, the bait would be gone and the trap empty
customer_reviews.author: Steve L. Pelletier

customer_reviews.title: These traps are useless!! The mouse cleaned the peanut butter from ...
customer_reviews.text: These traps are useless!! The mouse cleaned the peanut butter from the cup and got away. Also, after you rebait a few times, the trap will no longer stay open at all. 2 weeks in and I've thrown 2 away already b/c they won't stay open.
customer_reviews.author: Angela Barrett

customer_reviews.title: Very effective trap.
customer_reviews.text: Great trap! However the removable food tray is weak and breaks easily.
customer_reviews.author: Ron D Cavaille

customer_reviews.title: They will take off a finger if you aren't careful
customer_reviews.text: These suckers do the trick! Wow. I don't want to say what I'm using them for because some idiots won't understand. Ha.
customer_reviews.author: BLACE

customer_reviews.title: Love the trap!
customer_reviews.text: Have used several of these. They really take care of the pesty critters. I have lost quite a few traps, seems foxes or coyoties drag the traps away and eat the critters. I wire them to a tent peg now.
customer_reviews.author: rlbcomputer

customer_reviews.title: Well made trap that is easy to set
customer_reviews.text: I recently found a rat in my pantry so I decided to buy some traps. I purchased a pack of four trap and baited them with peanut butter, bananas, and nuts like previous reviewers have suggested. It's been two week and I still haven't caught it but it feels like it is well made. It is also easy to bait and set. Hopefully I will catch that little critter soon.
customer_reviews.author: Steve Nguyen

customer_reviews.title: You really need an exterminator
customer_reviews.text: Rats know these devices an can easily out maneuver the trap.
customer_reviews.author: Thomas Pelly

customer_reviews.title: Great but 4 stars since one of them broke...
customer_reviews.text: These super powerful traps clamp down on the rats so hard and quick that I am sure they don't feel any pain.. I don't like rats and mice but I still don't want them to suffer. That being said, the spring action is so strong that it actually broke one of the bait cups that attaches to the underside of the trap. Me - 5, Rats- 0.
customer_reviews.author: C. Ortiz

customer_reviews.title: Best Rat Trap Ever!
customer_reviews.text: These are awesome! Easy to use and easy to release dead rat from, into trash bag, to reuse again. No mess, no gross guts or blood to deal with. Worked so well, bought some for my parent's yard too.
customer_reviews.author: C. Bales

customer_reviews.title: Good Traps, Effective and Easy to Set
customer_reviews.text: Killed four rats the first night in use with these; they seem to be just as effective as traditional old snap traps and an improvement on that design. They are very easy to load and set without ever having to put your fingers in harm's way - I really like the removable bait cup that you load from the underside of the trap. They seem like they should hold up for a long time.
customer_reviews.author: Jon

customer_reviews.title: Buyer Beware of knock offs !!
customer_reviews.text: Amazon should double check these products. Working so quickly was a relief also because I was really concerned about the kids - the rat and just having traps out. Sleeping well now, and ready if another varmint wants to try it's luck.

product_meta.title: Bell Labs Trapper T-Rex Rat Trap (4 Traps)
product_meta.description: The Trapper T-Rex Rat Trap is a state-of-the-art mechanical trap that offers superior rat capture. Patented interlocking teeth make rat escape virtually impossible. With T-Rex you'll get the perfect combination of trigger sensitivity and trap velocity - speed and responsiveness that ensure a successful and deadly capture. Easy to set and safer to use than traditional snap traps, the T-Rex can be placed directly in a Protecta Rat Bait Station ( Sold Separately), or tied to pipes or beams that rats may use as highways. A bait cup in the center of the trigger pedal makes it easy to add baits including Bell's new Provoke Rat Attractant. (Sold Separately) USE: Place trap along baseboards or in a corner for best results. You can use nuts, nesting material like a small piece of cotton, or small amount of nutella in the trap for bait. Trapper T-REX offers superior rat capture. Patented, interlocking teeth make rat escapes virtually impossible. The trap is a perfect combination of trigger sensitivity and trap velocity -- speed and responsiveness ensure capture. Extensive field and laboratory testing fine-tuned Trapper T-REX to optimum specifications. Safer and easier to use than competitor's snap traps, Trapper T-REX can be readily set by foot safely on the ground. Press the trap open like a pedal, keeping fingers free and safe. Bell included a removable bait cup that inserts from the bottom of Trapper T-REX. The cup can be withdrawn and re-inserted without the trap being set, which greatly enhances safety and ease of use. You can use Trapper T-REX along a rat pathway. Or you can insert it into a tamper-resistant bait station.
feature_bullets: Listins is for 4 T-rex Rat Snap Traps. Target pests: Rats Dimensions: 5 1/2 in. x 3 in.

Application: Place trap near baseboards, corners, along walls, or in spaces where rodents are likely to travel. For discreet placement, two traps will fit in most Bell bait stations. Can also be placed alone or in pairs back-to-back along rat pathways, wired above ground to pipes or rafters
Pet safe: Should be used in places not readily accessible to pets and children to prevent tampering.

Special Features: Combines trigger sensitivity with the exact trap velocity needed to capture and hold rats, patented interlocking teeth make rat escapes virtually impossible, safer to use than other rat snap traps, sets easily by foot or hand, removable bait cup can be withdrawn, filled with an attractant and re-inserted without having the trap set
